        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 18 at 5:30AM CDT by NWS Tulsa OK</headline>
        <description>At 530 AM CDT, Doppler radar indicated a strong thunderstorm 3 miles
east of Avant, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation
is possible.

Locations in or near the path include...
Watova...                         Ramona...
Vera...                           Talala...
Oologah...                        Avant...
Foyil...                          Wolco...
Bushyhead...                      Skiatook...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
